title: Ex-Bulldog Fontaine Activated From IR for Wild
text:
Ex-Bulldog Fontaine Activated From IR for Wild 
By Zach Schneider Ex-Bulldog Fontaine Activated From IR for Wild October 14, 2015 Updated Oct 14, 2015 at 5:49 PM CDT 
St. Paul, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- Former University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) forward Justin Fontaine has been activated off injured reserve and will make his regular season debut for the Minnesota Wild on Thursday, the team announced on Wednesday morning. 
Fontaine had missed the first two games of the regular season after suffering an oblique injury during the preseason, making this the second straight year he's missed time at the start of the season.
